	"description": "When my son&#x27;s piano teacher told him he should use a metronome to practice\ntiming, I took it as an opportunity to learn Kotlin. I decided to learn the\nlanguage and Android&#x27;s ecosystem so I could build a Metronome app. \n\nMy initial implementation used a SeekBar to control BPM (Beats per Minute) — the\nrate at which the metronome ticks. \n\nHowever, as the project progressed, I wanted to make it resemble a physical\ndigital unit, as used by many musicians in the real physical world.\n\nPhysical units do",
